President Joseph R. Biden has issued an order to effectively implement the energy and infrastructure provisions in the Inflation Reduction Act of 2022. The Act aims to accelerate clean energy innovation, cut consumer energy costs, create jobs, promote environmental justice, and address the climate crisis. The order emphasizes the need for efficient use of public funds, reduction of greenhouse gas emissions, advancement of environmental and climate justice, promotion of clean energy generation and storage, strengthening of domestic manufacturing and supply chains, and coordination with various stakeholders. The order also establishes the White House Office on Clean Energy Innovation and Implementation and expands the National Climate Task Force to include implementation of the Act. The order is intended to be implemented in accordance with applicable laws and subject to the availability of appropriations.